            <h3>The Judging Framework</h3>
            <p>Panels of highly qualified industry professionals analyze performance across two core scoring tracks:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Execution & Technical Skill:</strong> Measures the physical synchronization, turn alignment, jump extension, placement consistency, and stamina of the dance roster.</li>
                <li><strong>Choreography & Presentation:</strong> Measures musicality, transition creativity, dynamic visuals, and overall visual effect.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section id="preparation" class="page-content">
            <h2 class="section-title">The Road to Orlando</h2>
            <p>Qualifying for and performing at the UDA National Championships at the ESPN Wide World of Sports Complex is a demanding multi-month commitment.</p>
            
            <div class="grid-3">
                <div class="card">
                    <h3>1. Summer Camp Qualification</h3>
                    <p>The journey begins in July or August. Teams must attend a mandatory UDA regional camp, master intensive curriculum, and earn a "Superior Trophy" designation or specific bids to qualify officially for nationals.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="card">
                    <h3>2. Autumn Choreography</h3>
                    <p>Choreographers are secured by late summer or early fall. Routines are completely structured and polished over hundreds of hours through the autumn academic calendar alongside game-day obligations.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="card">
                    <h3>3. The Elimination Track</h3>
                    <p>Once in Orlando, teams do not just perform once. They face intense multi-day schedules climbing from Preliminaries to Semi-Finals, before a highly selective fraction of teams secure a spot on the Finals floor.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

